        title: "Stop 4: Plaza de la Virgen",
        content: "<p>The Plaza de la Virgen is surrounded by the Basilica, the Cathedral and the Barrio de la Seu. </p><p>In the northern half of the square, the Neptune Fountain carved in bronze is particularly striking.<br>Known as the Neptune Fountain, it is the allegorical representation of the River Turia.<br>Neptune holds the cornucopia of abundance in his hand and is surrounded by female figures with Valencian farmer headdresses representing the main irrigation channels that water Valencia.</p><p>With which hand does Neptune hold the cornucopia?</p>"
