        id: "txt-Av1-P5-en", // mapa número 3
        title: "Stop 5: Plaza de la Virgen",
        content: "<p>In the background, the Gothic Door of the Cathedral stands out, the second to be built.<br>On its portico, every Thursday, the Water Tribunal is held; <br>a swift oral trial that settles disputes arising from the use and exploitation of irrigation water among farmers.<br>The origin of this tribunal, although unknown, is believed to have had a precedent in Roman times.<br>Its function as it operates today originated more than a millennium ago during Arab rule.</p><p><img src='imagenes/imagenes-aplicación/logo-alargado.png' alt='València be Guides' style='height:1.4em;vertical-align:baseline;position:relative;bottom:-0.2em;'> will provide you with detailed information about this area in Adventure number <mark>2</mark>.</p><p>How many figures surround the fountain?</p>"
